ild in a striped, multicolored cap and matching patterned clothing stands beside her. The girl’s expression softens into a small smile as she looks forward.\n\nOn a grassy soccer field, a blond child in a black athletic top with white stripes crouches in front of a goal net. A soccer ball blurs past near the child’s head. The child moves around the net, at one point appearing partly caught up or playfully tangled in it, then stands beneath the white mesh, looking upward and to the side with a serious, focused expression.\n\nTwo children stand together on a beach or sandy area, smiling broadly. Both wear matching bright blue T-shirts with large white letters reading “CLEAN PLANET CLUB.” One child raises a clear bag filled with collected trash, while the other lifts a blue bucket overhead. They lean shoulder to shoulder, proud and cheerful.\n\nThe commercial then shows children on BMX-style bicycles in a wooded outdoor area. They wear full helmets and colorful racing gear. Large number plates are fixed to the handlebars; one clearly reads “358,” and another partially visible plate reads “22.” The riders wait side by side, hands on the handlebars, looking ready to race.\n\nThe blond soccer child returns in a close portrait. A black-and-white soccer ball is held against the side of the child’s head, just above one shoulder. The child looks directly ahead, first with a steady, slightly skeptical expression, then with the beginning of a smile.\n\nThe final image is a clean product display on a white background: a green, white, and orange box of Fujicolor Super G film marked “200.” On the box, the words “FUJICOLOR” and “SUPER G” are visible. Beneath it, black text reads, “FUJI. A new way of seeing things.”",
